plugins.name: 数据生成图表可视化工具（专业版） Data Vision Chart Pro
plugins.description:
Introduction

This plugin enables users to create beautiful and interactive charts directly within Figma. Whether you need a bar, line, donut, or pie chart, the plugin offers real-time updates and customizable styles for seamless data visualization.


Function Description

  1. Create different chart types: Line, Bar, Donut, and Pie charts.
  2. Customize chart styles with predefined themes or use custom colors.
  3. Easily add, edit, and remove data rows with an intuitive interface.
  4. Export generated charts directly as Figma frames for further design use.
  5. Support for multiple languages, including English, Simplified Chinese, Traditional Chinese, Hindi, Japanese, and Korean.


Usage Instructions

  1. Select the chart type you want to create.
  2. Input the required data and choose a predefined color scheme or customize it.
  3. Set the chart dimensions (width and height) as per your design needs.
  4. Click "Generate Chart" to create the chart frame in Figma.
  5. Customize the chart further by adjusting colors and data points as needed.


Notes

  1. The plugin supports dynamic data updates and real-time chart previews.
  2. Ensure that all necessary data rows are filled to avoid incomplete chart generation.
  3. You can switch between chart types to explore different data visualizations.


介绍

此插件让用户可以直接在 Figma 中创建漂亮且交互式的图表。无论是柱状图、折线图、环形图还是饼图，插件都提供实时更新和自定义样式，助力轻松进行数据可视化。


功能说明

  1. 支持生成不同类型的图表：折线图、柱状图、环形图和饼图。
  2. 提供多种预设主题配色，或使用自定义颜色。
  3. 直观界面，轻松添加、编辑和删除数据行。
  4. 将生成的图表直接导出为 Figma 的框架，用于后续设计。
  5. 支持多种语言，包括英语、简体中文、繁体中文、印地语、日语和韩语。


使用方法

  1. 选择您需要创建的图表类型。
  2. 输入所需数据，选择预设配色或自定义颜色。
  3. 根据设计需要设置图表尺寸（宽度和高度）。
  4. 点击“生成图表”按钮，即可在 Figma 中创建图表框架。
  5. 您可以根据需要进一步调整图表的颜色和数据点。


注意事项

  1. 插件支持动态数据更新和实时图表预览。
  2. 确保所有必要的数据行已填写完整，以避免生成不完整的图表。
  3. 您可以在不同的图表类型之间切换，探索不同的数据可视化效果。

accepted.name: KingweiCheung
accepted.description: If you have any questions or suggestions, feel free to contact me at kingweichueng@qq.com.

plugins.tagline: Generate stunning charts for data visualization with ease

plugins.name: UXtweak: Prototype Usability Testing
plugins.description:
With the UXtweak Prototype Usability Testing Plugin, you can easily turn your designs and prototypes into powerful user testing studies—right from Figma. 


Making it simple to gather invaluable user feedback for identifying and resolving issues before they impact development. 


The plugin ensures quick, reliable, and optimized import of even your largest and most complex Figma files, preserving all interactions and animations, while offering the flexibility to test specific flows or entire prototypes.


How it works:

  1. Open your Figma file.
  2. Click Share and copy the file link (set to “Anyone with the link can view”).
  3. Go to UXtweak and create a Prototype Testing study.
  4. In the Designs tab, paste your Figma file link.
  5. Copy the generated plugin link.
  6. Open the UXtweak Figma plugin and paste it in.
  7. Choose the flows you want to import and click Import.


Your prototype will be ready to test in UXtweak—no exports, no uploads, just seamless usability testing.


Key features: 


The plugin offers features to cover every aspect of your prototype usability testing needs.

  1. Seamless Figma integration: Quick import of your Figma prototypes, preserving designs and transitions.  
  2. Flexible study setup: Define custom tasks, add follow-up questions (survey) with skip logic (branching), and randomize task order.  
  3. Qualitative feedback: Capture screen, voice, and even face recordings to understand both what users do and why. Export videos in MP4 format for easy sharing.  
  4. Diverse recruitment options: Utilize our User Panel to recruit targeted participants for your studies, leverage your own database of users, or share a simple link.  
  5. Clickmaps & Heatmaps: Analyze clicks and identify hot spots to understand user attention.  
  6. Path analysis: Track exact user journeys, revealing where users get lost or deviate from expected flows.  
  7. Funnel view: Gain a detailed understanding of participant drop-off points.  
  8. Session replay: Replay full user sessions to observe behavior in context.  


Start for free at https://www.uxtweak.com/ or learn more about the plugin in our Knowledge Hub.
plugins.tagline: Turn your designs and prototypes into powerful user testing studies on UXtweak—right from Figma.

plugins.name: Variable Copy Paste & Export
plugins.description:
Simple plugin that copies and pastes variables between files. Copied variables can also be exported into CSV format.


HOW TO USE:

  1. Open the plugin and hit "Copy Variables". The copied collections and modes should then appear in the plugin UI.
  2. Go to the file you want to paste to, open the plugin and hit "Paste".
  3. Double-check that the pasted variables match the original. Sometimes they get pasted out of order.
  4. Copied variables can also be exported by hitting "Export" and then clicking on the "Download CSV" link that appears underneath.


PLEASE NOTE: Aliases that reference external (non-local) variables will not work and will be shown in the console if found. Also, pasted variables may not always end up in their original order- I am not a dev and don't know why this happens (if anyone can help, please reach out!!!)
plugins.tagline: Paste variables between files and export to CSV

plugins.name: Chartify
plugins.description:
Chartify is a powerful yet simple plugin that helps you turn spreadsheet data into clean, customizable charts — directly in Figma.


Just upload a file or paste a public Google Sheets link, and Chartify will generate a beautiful chart that fits right into your design.


What Chartify can do:

  1. Supports data from:
  2. CSV, TSV, Excel (.xlsx/.xls)
  3. Google Sheets (public links)
  4. HTML tables, XML, Word (.docx), PDF, and more
  5. 6 chart types:
  6. Line
  7. Smooth Line
  8. Column
  9. Bar
  10. Pie
  11. Donut
  12. Smart customization options:
  13. Auto layout support
  14. Figma Variables for styles
  15. Optional axes, grid, and legends
  16. Responsive and consistent with your design system



How to use:

  1. Open the plugin.
  2. Upload a data file or paste a public Google Sheets URL.
  3. (Optional) Enter the sheet name.
  4. Choose the chart type.
  5. Adjust settings: auto layout, variables, axes, and legend.
  6. Click Generate — your chart will appear directly on the canvas.


Chartify is built for designers who need to visualize data fast — without leaving Figma.

accepted.name: Andrei Kuznetsov
accepted.description: Templates, UI Kits, Design Systems, Plugins

plugins.tagline: Effortless Data Charts in Figma

plugins.name: TokenWizard
plugins.description:
TokenWizard is your all-in-one starter tool for building consistent, scalable design systems in Figma. With just one click, it generates structured design tokens as Figma variables, creates corresponding color, text, and spacing styles, and even renders a beautiful visual palette preview right on your canvas.


Whether you're building a brand system from scratch or bringing order to design chaos, TokenWizard adapts to your needs. Choose which token types to include (Color, Spacing, Typography), pick base colors from the UI, and skip the hassle of manual setup. No duplicate styles, no redundant variables — everything is smartly created or updated in-place.


Designed for UX teams, solo designers, and developers alike, TokenWizard transforms repetitive setup into a streamlined, creative experience — so you can start designing with structure in minutes, not hours.

plugins.name: Align Auto Layout
plugins.description:
MacOS shortcut setup:

System Settings → Keyboard → Keyboard Shortcuts → App Shortcuts → “+”.

App: Figma.

Menu Title:

plugins.name: Pinnaflow Collections
plugins.description:
Figma CMS Table Generator helps you structure CMS data directly in your Figma file, and export it as a Webflow-compatible CSV.


With this plugin, you can:


🗂 Create CMS Collections

Define fields with types like Plain Text, Rich Text, Image, Number, Date, or Switch — all directly in your Figma UI.


🧩 Add CMS Items

Populate data using a form-driven interface. Each item becomes a variant within your CMS component.


📤 Export CSV for Webflow

Download a ready-to-import CSV with your data structured according to Webflow CMS standards.


🎯 Apply CMS Data to Design

Inject field values into selected Figma elements by choosing collection, item, and field — no copy-pasting.


⚡ Real-Time Preview & Auto Validation

Live feedback lets you know when your component is ready for export, and disables the export button if any structure is invalid.


🖼 Responsive & Intuitive UI

A clean and responsive layout, with tooltips, modals, and auto-tab interactions for seamless workflow.


🛠 How to use:

Create a Collection

Go to the "Create Collection" tab → enter a collection name → define fields → click "Create Collection".


Add Items

Switch to "Create Item" → fill in values for each defined field → click "Create Item".


Export to CSV

Select the CMS component → click "Export CSV" in the Collection tab.


Apply Data to UI

In "Apply Data" tab → choose collection, item, and field → select a text layer in your design → click "Apply to Selected Element".


✅ Best Practices

Your CMS component must contain a frame named “CMS Properties”, with text layers in the format:

Field Name | Field Type


When applying data, make sure the selected element is a single text node.


Only one CMS component should be selected at a time when creating items or exporting.


Use consistent field names and valid types for clean CSV output and Webflow compatibility.
plugins.tagline: Create CMS collections in Figma and export them for Webflow import

plugins.description:
Transform any Figma design into a complete set of perfectly scaled Chrome extension icons in seconds.


Benefits:

  1. Save hours of manual work - No more tedious resizing and exporting
  2. Perfect proportions - Maintains design integrity across all sizes
  3. Professional results - Vector paths, text, and effects scale beautifully
  4. Chrome extension ready - Standard sizes (16px, 24px, 36px, 48px, 128px)
  5. Batch processing - Handle multiple designs simultaneously

  1. Select your design - Choose any frame, group, component, or instance
  2. Run Iconize - Go to Plugins → Iconize → Scale to Icon Sizes

Perfect for Chrome extensions, web apps, mobile apps, and any project requiring multiple icon sizes. Works with complex designs including vectors, text, effects, and nested elements.

plugins.name: BrowserLens
plugins.description:
This plugin lets you import color styles from the BrowserLens web extension. Insert colors as layers in your design and add palettes to your local styles.


Learn more about BrowserLens: https://browserlens.com/

Documentation: https://docs.browserlens.com/


How to Use

  1. Open any webpage with the BrowserLens extension.
  2. Click export > Figma (BrowserLens Plugin).
  3. Download the style file for Figma.
  4. Run this plugin and upload the style file.
  5. Choose whether to add colors as local styles.
  6. Click 'Import Styles'.


About BrowserLens


BrowserLens is a web extension designed to extract styling and seo information from any webpage without the need for developer tools. It provides a simple UI for extracting and copying webpage information from the current tab.


Extension Features

  1. ⌨️ View fonts used on a webpage and the associated CSS values.
  2. 🖌️ Extract colors from a webpage and click to copy color value.
  3. 🌅 Extract gradients from a webpage and click to copy CSS value.
  4. 🎨 Export color palettes to Figma.
  5. 🌐 Preview SEO data including page meta, OpenGraph tags and Twitter Card data.
  6. ✅ Check SEO meta for best practices including title and description length.
  7. 🖼️ List all images present on a page and click to download, including background images.
  8. 🌃 Dark mode support.

plugins.name: Figma to osu!framework
plugins.description:
A third-party plugin to convert Figma elements to osu!framework code


Supported features:

  1. Basic layout (RelativeSizeAxes, Anchor/Orign, Padding, etc.)
  2. Converting cornerRadius to masking containers
  3. Linear Gradients (Both simple as well as multi-stop gradients work as long as they're horizontal or vertical)
  4. Text (Only one style per text element supported)
plugins.tagline: Convert Figma elements into osu!framework snippets

plugins.name: Badenova Design System Sync
plugins.description:
This plugin synchronizes your Figma tokens with the Badenova Design System


Usage:

You need to provide a valid GitHub token to synchronize your Figma tokens.

To obtain a GitHub token, contact christoph.hummel@badenova.de or generate your own token.


If you have a valid GitHub token, enter it into the respective input field and press Save.

Then, click the Sync Badenova Design-Tokens button.

If the synchronization is successful, you will receive a confirmation message.
plugins.tagline: Synchronize your Figma tokens with the Badenova Design System

plugins.name: frameToGroup
plugins.description:
frameToGroup converts frames into organised groups while retaining essential visual properties.


✨ Key Features

✅ Effortless Conversion – Convert frames into neatly structured groups while keeping fills, strokes, and effects intact.

✅ Nested Frame Handling – Automatically processes nested frames for a well-organised layer structure.

✅ Style Preservation – Retains local styles and effects using asynchronous processing.

✅ User-Friendly UI – Simple, intuitive interface with one-click conversion.

✅ Continuous Workflow – Keep the plugin open for multiple conversions without interruptions.


✨ How to Use

  1. Select the frames you wish to convert in your Figma document.
  2. Click "Convert Frames to Groups" in the plugin UI.
plugins.tagline: Convert Frames to Groups While Retaining Styles
